> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A morphism of schemes `f : X ⟶ Y` is flat if for each affine `U ⊆ Y` and\n`V ⊆ f ⁻¹' U`, the induced map `Γ(Y, U) ⟶ Γ(X, V)` is flat. This is equivalent to\nasking that all stalk maps are flat (see `AlgebraicGeometry.Flat.iff_flat_stalkMap`).\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/AlgebraicGeometry/Morphisms/Flat.html#AlgebraicGeometry.Flat","kind":"class","line":37,"name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Flat","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/AlgebraicGeometry/Morphisms/Flat.lean#L37-L45"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Algebra.Category.Ring.Under.Limits","Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.Morphisms.Affine","Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.Properties","Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.PullbackCarrier","Mathlib.RingTheory.RingHom.FaithfullyFlat"],"instances":[{"className":"AlgebraicGeometry.HasRingHomProperty","name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Flat.instHasRingHomPropertyFlat","typeNames":["AlgebraicGeometry.Flat"]},{"className":"AlgebraicGeometry.Flat","name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Flat.instOfIsOpenImmersion","typeNames":[]},{"className":"CategoryTheory.MorphismProperty.IsStableUnderComposition","name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Flat.instIsStableUnderCompositionScheme","typeNames":["AlgebraicGeometry.Flat"]},{"className":"AlgebraicGeometry.Flat","name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Flat.comp","typeNames":["CategoryTheory.CategoryStruct.comp"]},{"className":"CategoryTheory.MorphismProperty.IsMultiplicative","name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Flat.instIsMultiplicativeScheme","typeNames":["AlgebraicGeometry.Flat"]},{"className":"CategoryTheory.MorphismProperty.IsStableUnderBaseChange","name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Flat.isStableUnderBaseChange","typeNames":["AlgebraicGeometry.Flat"]},{"className":"AlgebraicGeometry.Flat","name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Flat.instFstScheme","typeNames":["CategoryTheory.Limits.pullback.fst"]},{"className":"AlgebraicGeometry.Flat","name":"AlgebraicGe